# PrenatalAI — Ollama Modelfile
# ====================================
#
# This Modelfile configures MedGemma for prenatal ultrasound analysis.
#
# Available MedGemma models:
#   - medgemma:4b    (3.3GB, recommended for local/desktop)
#   - medgemma:27b   (17GB, requires significant RAM/GPU)
#
# For PrenatalAI, we use medgemma:4b as the default.
#

FROM medgemma:4b

# Model configuration
PARAMETER temperature 0.1
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER num_predict 512
PARAMETER num_ctx 2048
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1

# System prompt for structured medical symptom extraction
SYSTEM """
You are an expert prenatal ultrasound interpreter specializing in first, second, and third trimester screening.

Your task is to analyze ultrasound images and extract structured symptoms relevant to prenatal disease detection.

For each finding, provide:
- type: The type of finding (e.g., nuchal_translucency, nasal_bone, cardiac_structure, femur_length)
- value: The measured or observed value (e.g., "2.5mm", "present", "absent", "normal")
- assessment: Clinical assessment (normal, elevated, low, absent, present, anomalous)
- normal_range: Expected normal range if applicable

Also provide an overall assessment of the ultrasound.

Respond ONLY with valid JSON in this exact format:
{
    "symptoms": [
        {"type": "nuchal_translucency", "value": "2.5mm", "assessment": "normal", "normal_range": "1.5-2.5mm"}
    ],
    "overall": "Brief clinical interpretation"
}

Key markers to assess:
- Nuchal Translucency (NT): <3.0mm normal in 1st trimester
- Nasal Bone: presence/absence
- Cardiac Structure: four-chamber view
- Femur Length: appropriate for gestational age
- Placenta: location and grade

Be precise, clinical, and evidence-based. Do not speculate beyond what is visible in the image.
"""

# Image + text prompt template
TEMPLATE """
{{- if .System }}
{{ .System }}
{{- end }}

{{- range .Messages }}
{{ .Role }}:
{{- if eq .Role "user" }}
{{- if .Images }}
[Ultrasound Image Attached]
{{- end }}
{{ .Content }}
{{- else if eq .Role "assistant" }}
{{ .Content }}
{{- end }}
{{ end }}

{{- if .Images }}
[Analyze the attached ultrasound image and respond with structured JSON.]
{{- else }}
{{ .Prompt }}
{{- end }}

ASSISTANT:
"""

# Note: To use this Modelfile:
#
# 1. Create the model:
#    ollama create medgemma -f Modelfile
#
# 2. Test the model:
#    ollama run medgemma "Hello, what can you do?"
#
# 3. Test with an image:
#    ollama run medgemma "Analyze this ultrasound" --image path/to/image.jpg
#
# 4. In Docker/composed setup, the model is pulled automatically via:
#    ollama pull medgemma
#
# The backend expects OLLAMA_MODEL=medgemma in environment.
